Luke and Linus react to fresh Battlefield 6 news: persistent servers are returning (via Portal) and two vehicle-heavy maps are coming to the next playtest. They break down why server browsers matter, why big maps/vehicles defined old-school Battlefield, complaints about bot fill and small maps in the beta, and interesting class tweaks (OP medic paddles, sniper headshot = permadeath).

Watch the full WAN Show: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DzvhAMHF_dY
